  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 6. Substituting y = 5x + 2 into 5y = 17x \u2212 6: 5(5x + 2) = 17x \u2212 6, so 25x + 10 = 17x \u2212 6, giving x = \u22122. Then y = 5(\u22122) + 2 = \u22128. So x \u2212 y = \u22122 \u2212 (\u22128) = 6.</p>",
